The Issue: A new remote-work policy was launched without a security review.

The Solution: A risk assessment using the 7 steps of the NIST RMF.

NIST-RMF-Assessment.md]

1. Prepare: Established the organizational risk tolerance for remote access.
2. Categorize: Labeled "Client Case Files" as High Impact for confidentiality.
3. Select: Chose NIST SP 800-53 controls (e.g., AC-2 Account Management).
4. Implement: Enabled mandatory VPN and Disk Encryption (FileVault/BitLocker).
5. Assess: Verified that encryption was active on all remote laptops.
